FBIS4-41229 "drsov121_b_94020" FBIS-SOV-94-121 Daily Report 22 Jun 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Military Issues Yeltsin Signs Decree on Use of Border Troops Yeltsin Signs Decree on Use of Border Troops LD2206210694 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1900 GMT 22 Jun 94 LD2206210694 Moscow Radio Rossii Network Russian BFN [Text] Boris Yeltsin has signed a decree on Russian servicemen as border troops taking part in work based on the international legal demarcation of the state border of the Russian Federation. This has been reported by the president's press service. In accordance with the document, border troops engaged in this work are being sent to carry out their military service to a department of the international legal demarcation of the state border, which is being set up within the Main Command of Border Troops. The decree provides for measures for the social protection of the servicemen during their transfer to the new department.
